 THE Caretaker Committee of the All Progressives Congress (APC) has constituted reconciliation committees for Edo and Ondo states. The party’s Deputy National Publicity Secretary, Mr. Yekini Nabena, in a statement on Tuesday in Abuja, said the committee for Edo would be led by former Senate president Ken Nnamani, while Niger State Governor Abubakar Bello would head the reconciliation committee for Ondo State. “This is in line with the process of true reconciliation among leaders and members of the party at all levels, announced by the National Chairman of the Caretaker/Extra-Ordinary National Convention Planning Committee, Governor Mai Mala Buni. “Members of Edo reconciliation committee headed by Nnamani include the Minister of Works and Housing, Mr. Babatunde Raji Fashola and the Minister of State for Labour, Mr. Fetus Keyamo. “Others are Prof. Tahir Mamman, Mrs. Margaret Okadigbo, Mr. Sanusi Musa and Mr. Abdul-Rahman Kawu Sumaila as secretary. “Members of the Ondo State reconciliation committee headed by Bello include Sen. Adamu Aliero, Sen. Bamidele Opeyemi and Mr. Gambon Magaji. “Others are Mr. Jasper Azuwatalum, Hajiya Binta Muazu, Mr. Iquo Inyang and Mr. Shina Pellar as secretary,” Nabena said.